==English==
===Etymology===
''[[know]]'' + ''[[-est]]'', the archaic second-person singular present tense suffix

===Verb form===
'''knowest'''
# {{archaic}} [[second-person singular]] form of ''to [[know]]''.
#:''Give a portion to seven, and also to eight; for thou '''knowest''' not what evil shall be upon the earth.'' - [[Ecclesiastes]] 11:2